full_text:
Ok, let's take a look at Chiefs snaps by week. TE's first. Same story all season long. Kelce, then Gray, then Fortson. Doubt this changes much. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/JHG87Fh1Ys

Wide Receivers next. JuJu's snaps and snap % both on an upward trend last three weeks. Watson and MVS both holding pretty steady. Skyy's snap % is dropping slightly, but overall count is rising a bit. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/Z8BQ3MXRvQ

Running backs. Pacheco lost some snaps due to that fumble of his in the 2nd quarter. That allowed Jet to continue to put distance between them. Jet has been top dog 5 of the last 6 weeks. Doubt that changes, though the split probably shifts closer to 50-50. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/JBf6DdiLra

Defense next. Cornerbacks. Williams snaps have fallen off a cliff last two weeks, though that's partly because we've run less 3 CB snaps. He and Watson are splitting snaps right now. Hopefully just to keep both sharp for the postseason. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/lMSuaUc8GU

Safeties. Not much here, honestly. It's Reid and Juan, and then Cook fills in occasionally. We don't run much 3 safety looks, so that's pretty much the story here. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/AaGwqVMKfe

Linebackers. Harris only took a partial series from Gay this week, though it was a long one. Chenal got more run, I assume because HOU was using a lot of heavy personnel. Bolton got all the snaps, as usual. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/S2uVH1r1Ze

Interior Defensive Line, aka can anyone on the team not named Jones crack 50% of the snaps? The answer is nope, though Saunders has flirted with it. Jones's snaps have dropped the last two weeks. Wonder if they're trying to keep him fresh for playoffs. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/NavkUG579E

Finally, defensive ends. Clark still leading the group. Karlaftis still on his generally downward slope since week 10. Danna and Dunlap both getting solid snap counts. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/bjHHwYVMjw

Some fans have already started rooting for a higher draft pick. The #1 pick is quite likely already decided. But what about the rest of the top 5 picks? Here are all teams whose top 5 probability is at least 1%.
#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/MDB1gnYtbp

Day 57: Today I'm sharing the top 20 players by Red Zone volume and their TD efficiency. Data from #nflverse and created using #SQL. #100DaysOfCode 

First up, standings through Week 15, ordered by number of Red Zone plays (descending): https://t.co/qsbEIr7DXu
